84 def reconstruct_path(parents, start, goal, order='forward'):
85  # parents are now in index
86 
87  current = goal
88  path = []
89  while current != start:
90  path.append(current)
91  current = parents[current]
92  path.append(start)
93  if order == 'forward':
94  path.reverse()
95 
96  return np.array(path)

98 def path_length(path):
99  # compute costs
100  diff_ = np.diff(path, axis=0)
101  hyp_ = np.hypot(diff_[:,0], diff_[:,1])
102  dist_ = sum(hyp_)
103  return dist_
